Procrastinated on student gifts this year. On top of getting out a little earlier than normal and having to take some unexpected time off before break, I put ornaments together for them the night before I needed them. 😬 I had nothing prepared, so I ran to Walmart in a scramble and spent about $12 in total. 👏🏼

🎄Glass ornaments from Walmart - $5 for 8
🎄Inside is a student picture, “nice list” with our class list, and random words that describe our class on strips of paper (third is the word, 3, class family, love, I matter, student name, 2022-2023)
🎄Tied with string (also Walmart) and a laminated name tag made by me
🎄Done!

Also, don’t be fooled. This took a lot longer than I planned and I was hoping they would be a little cuter. OH WELL! On break now. When do you start break?

Something about fresh name tags and a tidied classroom to start the new year. ✨ 

I have a bundle of name tags in my TPT! 😊 Link in highlight!

The easiest, best sweet treat! 🍰 

Recipe from @gatheredliving. ❤️ Link to recipe in stories & highlights!

A few highs and a whole lot of lows. Grateful for the lessons this year taught me, but I’m beyond ready for a new year.

A “part day” in the life of a teacher that’s happy it’s finally March! 🍀 Also, can you find how many times you can hear my name being said in the background of this Reel???? 🤪

On a scale of 1-10, how prepared do you feel each day as a teacher (10 being fully prepared)? 

I mean, I could use a full week, with no students, to just plan and prep for the following week and still wouldn’t feel prepared. 

One thing I’ve learned as a teacher is ya just gotta go for it. You’re never going to be fully prepared. And sometimes I feel I teach the best when it’s not planned and thought out. 

Is this just me? Please tell me no. 😅

Teachers need more plan and prep time!!
Lately… ☕️ 👚 💅🏼 edition

Back to rows we go! It’s state testing season! 🫠🥵

I hate rows, but we really should always be in rows because #focus.

A day in the life of a teacher who has to take a half day for an appointment and…

🫠stresses about leaving work early
🫠has a million teacher thoughts running through the brain on way to said appointment
🫠gets to said appointment wondering how I made it safely because my brain won’t stop running
🫠makes a plan to come home after appointment to get a million work things done but…

❤️ends up at Target and Starbucks. 

There’s always tomorrow morning for my teacher work stresses to go right back through the roof, right???? 🫠 Don’t worry, it will because there’s always 1,000+ high-priority things on a teacher’s to-do list this time of year. 🙃🙃🙃

The fact that I don’t have a countdown until summer yet is insane because I’ve never been more ready. 😰 If you’re feeling overwhelmed, exhausted, and have very little motivation, I’M WITH YA!!!!

This is your reminder to save the newspapers (if you can even find them anymore) for this Earth Day project! We will do ours next week when our school does all of our weeklong Earth Week activities! 🌎💙♻️ See my highlights for a how-to.

Was so happy to put on my brand new @lipsticklittles sweatshirt this morning, and who would’ve known the secret message inside the sleeve was already working on me as I spilled bacon grease on myself at 6am this morning. You better believe I quick spot treated it and wore it to school!

Buy yourself this sweatshirt because we all known we need this reminder every 5 minutes this time of year! (Plus she has 20% today!) 

You got this, teachers! I just started my countdown, and we are at 23 DAYS! ☀️ (But really 21 days for me because this teacher will be using 2 personal days between now and then!) How many days do you have left?!

We are celebrating Earth Week 🌎 at our school this week. A coworker shared this book and activity with me and it will be a keeper for years to come! Sharing a link to the handout in stories + will save it to my Earth Week highlight! 🌎♻️💙

Countdown totally inspired by my coworker @miss5th! My favorite part of this countdown is how its focus is on celebrating our classmates. 💜 Because my students could very well have @miss5th as a teacher in 2 years, I try not to steal all her ideas, but it’s hard not to! I plan on using the poster to write kind and thoughtful notes to our classmates, line leader for that day, pick a sticker, *maybe spin our birthday wheel*, and a few other special perks. I’d love to hear below what special activities, countdowns, or celebrations you do at the end of the year!

🌎♻️💙

One other tip that I didn’t include — I always prep this activity by picking out the pieces of paper myself. We all know the world that we’re living in and how the news typically is 90% negative, so be cautious and observant when picking pieces for your students to use! Also, I steer clear of the obituaries page!
☀️saturday plans • peach cold brew 🍑

Decided last week scheduling a personal day was 100% necessary. So, the last 24 hours have been pretty darn perfect, as expected! ☀️ Kenny, Kelsea, friends, family, coffee, flowers, greasy food, warm, sunny weather, good music, & a day away from work. 💯 

This school year quite literally started out day 1 pretty damn hard. It has been extremely challenging & exhausting for me for a variety of reasons. I still whole-heartedly love my job - 100% - but today completely felt like a true summer day to me & MAN. I’ve NEVER been more ready for a summer break than now. 

FIFTEEN DAYS TO SWEET SUMMERTIME! ☀️😎👙🕶️🌸
Day in the life of a teacher in the month of May…kinda. But not really. 😅 Surviving, not thriving over here!!! 🫠
There are many emotions and moments of reflection that an end to a school year brings, and this one has definitely carried a lot! So, here’s my confirmation I made it through year 9! 😴 🥳

Went to Walmart for body wash… 🫠 

First official day of summer break and I’m already buying things I DON’T need! 😅

This year is about to ✨hit different✨ with my smallest class ever! Had 13, one just got added, so I’m at a grand total of 14! 🥹 It’s about to be a good year! 🎉 Probably will be my smallest class ever. How many students are on your roster?
Never enough rugs when your classroom carpet is probably older than you are. 🫠 Butttt, new floor next year!
Today was the day of classroom setup where things got better and not worse!! 👏🏼 I LOVE when this day comes and I can finally calm down a little. 😅

I get a message from MY KINDERGARTEN teacher every fall when I head back into the classroom — the teacher I was so lucky to have as a 5-year-old little girl. My heart bursts every August when I receive her message. It’s teachers like her that inspire, motivate, and most importantly, remind me that we ARE making a difference in our students’ lives. I know that because she has, without a doubt, done that for me. ❤️🥹
And then it was ten. About to be a full  decade in the classroom. Please someone tell me, where has the time gone?!
Day 1 with my 15 students starts tomorrow! Ready or not, here we go!

Every morning is a game to see how much I can get done before the students walk in. So here’s a peek + some random live photo moments (some I didn’t even mean to capture) from our Thursday. ⭐️

•The moment I get rolling on my to-do list in the morning is when the kids start walking in. 😅
•I get to school usually about 10-15 minutes before contract time.
•Parents (+grandparents this year), truly don’t know how much I appreciate donations from my wish list. It’ll never change, but I always feel guilty asking for things and 100% shouldn’t.
•This past week I realized probably 5 items I didn’t have on my wish list that I truly needed more than anything else. Typical. So I went and bought them. 🫠
•Bugs that collect in my drawers are never-ending. 🤢
•Taking a video while doing something in the other hand is very challenging. Probably as hard as Saving Fred. 😂
•The amount of things you realize need changing after 1 week into school literally never ends. But honestly it never stops. I’ll be changing things in May still.
•Those cough drops I was using last week I don’t think were from just talking too much. Week 1 got the best of me & editing this Reel is literally all I got accomplished this weekend. 😴🤧
•But here’s to getting lots of rest + hopefully a week of not feeling like I have 0 energy. 😆

Do we relate with anything? Share below! 😊

Goodnight from me and my annoying doorbell. 🤪

Lol no, but kind of. For those asking how I attach my doorbell to my lanyard - it’s taped to the back of an old badge! I needed a new doorbell (I’ve had mine for years) & this one came with 999 annoying sounds and 1 simple one. 🫠 And all I need is 1 simple sound, so it’ll work. 👌🏼

Did I add a few Taylor stickers to the store? Of course.
Was today supposed to be our first Sticker Store? Yes.
Did we have it? No.
Am I trying to stay firm with behaviors & not give 3 and 4 chances. Yes.

Sticking to behaviors/consequences/holding true to your word can be hard. Especially at the beginning of the year when your trying to build relationships from the ground up. 🙃 But we will try again next week!

Also, every year is different for what stickers kids gravitate towards. Last year, animals seemed to be the hit. Along with Taylor once I got a pack of her stickers. 😂 Interested to see what they like this year! Luckily, I finally got stickers on my wish list this year, and hopefully with what I was supplied with will last us all year long! Very grateful for generous parents! 💛
23-24 classroom with background vocals from Taylor (Taylor’s Version) 💜

Also, who caught the comment about inside recess?? 😅🫠

Who doesn’t love & appreciate a little happy mail? 💌 I try to secretly stick a happy note in my students’ desks as often as possible to show them I DO notice the great things they are doing, even though I might not say it all of the time.

I just posted this, along with a happy mail tracker (for parent communication) in my TPT. 💕
My 🎁 tonight = enjoying the first night of break by doing absolutely nothing!

2024 GRATITUDE REMINDER 🤎 It's not about what I have to do, but what I GET to do. It's easy to get negative in all aspects of life. I do every day. Taking a moment to reflect on the things I need to be more mindful of. 🌟 

🤎 I get to go to a job that pays my bills.
🤎 I get to brush my hair in the morning.
🤎 I get to put groceries in my fridge.
🤎 I get to learn from this student which will help me grow as an educator. 
🤎 I get to go to the gym.
🤎 I get to shovel the snow.
🤎 I get to live a healthy life, having access to healthcare when needed.

I think of the opposites of those situations. Of people that don't have those opportunities to begin with. Working on being more aware & doing more self-reflection before I start to complain. You never know how your complaints might make others feel. 

The list of reminders is never-ending.

Share what you GET to do. Let's spread some valuable reminders. 🤎

#PositiveMindset #Mindfulness #Gratitude
